KC Hart 19 May 2019
.
Before KC & I were together he ODed. I wouldn't find out for a few days, but it didn't matter per se, because the night it happened I felt such grief in the middle of my body, I- in the middle of my bed and close to sleep- began to sob. 
.
The energetic- & most relevant connection- I have with KC bears its own weight when it comes to his recovering heroin addiction. 
But of course, there are many other very tangible elements which prove to be far more immediately suffocating. 
Like, knowing your partner neither cares enough for his own life to stay alive, nor seemingly yours for being able to leave it so easily. 
The degree of loss one can meet within the confines of addiction is something no rational & feeling human being would ever wish on anyone. 
.
Today was one of those days, a milestone if we can let it be. I love you, KC. I feel grateful to be here with you now. There can be healing in that, there is healing in that. 
.
